<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Reeve described this species from &quot;Mus. Dennison&quot;, and said it was identical to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="I.Lea" authorityYear="1838" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="decoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Bulimus decoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lea, 1838 (not 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Férussac">Ferussac</normalizedToken>
, 1821); he referred to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lea’s">Lea's</normalizedToken>
figure (pl. 23 fig. 8). The specimens found correspond to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Reeve’s">Reeve's</normalizedToken>
description, but none can be matched to the shell figured on his plate 44.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
